content.html: Swift understands this. JS does not. -12219296400 is the timestamp 1 hour before the beginning of October 15, 1582 (UTC). That means it should be October 4, 23:00 hours, because of the skipped days. JS gives back October 14, 1582. A day that did not exist.
content.value:
Swift understands this. JS does not.

-12219296400 is the timestamp 1 hour before the beginning of October 15, 1582 (UTC). That means it should be October 4, 23:00 hours, because of the skipped days.

JS gives back October 14, 1582. A day that did not exist.
